# JangLabs — multi-lab workspace marker.
#
# Presence of this file marks the directory as a multi-lab workspace. The
# lab-scope hook (claude/hooks/lab-scope.sh, symlinked to ~/.claude/hooks/ by
# claude/install.sh) walks UP from a session's working directory to find this
# marker. When found, it treats every immediate non-dot child directory (except
# the sanctioned build/ output dir) as an independent lab scope and, the moment
# the active lab changes, injects a short banner pointing at that lab's
# authoritative entry doc (its CLAUDE.md, which overrides this workspace root).
#
# Only the file's PRESENCE is load-bearing; everything below is documentation
# the hook does not parse. Keep it a dotfile so it doesn't count as a lab.
name: JangLabs
entry-doc-precedence: CLAUDE.md AGENTS.md README.md HANDOFF.md
non-lab-dirs: build
